{
  "texts": [
    "The remainder of this paper is organized as follows.",
    "Section 2 analyzes two fundamental paradigms in human-machine collaboration-the multi-agent approach and the Centaurian onein light of the recent resurgence of agentic AI.",
    "Section 3 provides foundational background on Petri nets and their extensions.",
    "Section 4 introduces the concept of communication spaces as a unifying framework for these paradigms, grounded in formal architectures and coordination mechanisms.",
    "Sections 5 and 6 illustrate these ideas with two use cases, demonstrating how communication spaces can be applied in practical HCI scenarios."
  ]
}